# ERB Template Standards

> **Design system:** nitro-web uses Playbook exclusively — all UI is built with `pb_rails()` helpers. See `frontend-development.mdc` for the full design system rules and component selection. See `playbook-components.mdc` for prop reference.

## Use Playbook UI Helpers

Always use `pb_rails()` Playbook helpers for UI components instead of raw HTML:

```erb
<%# GOOD - Playbook components %>
<%= pb_rails("card") do %>
  <%= pb_rails("title", props: { text: "Hello", size: 3 }) %>
  <%= pb_rails("body", props: { text: "Content here" }) %>
<% end %>

<%= pb_rails("button", props: { text: "Submit", variant: "primary" }) %>

<%= pb_rails("flex", props: { justify: "between" }) do %>
  <%= pb_rails("flex_item") { "Left" } %>
  <%= pb_rails("flex_item") { "Right" } %>
<% end %>
```

## No Inline JavaScript

Never put JavaScript directly in templates:
```erb
<%# BAD %>
<script>
  $(document).ready(function() { ... });
</script>

<%# GOOD - put JS in assets directory %>
<%= javascript_include_tag "my_feature" %>
```

## ERB Lint Compliance

All ERB files must pass `erb_lint`. Common rules:
- Proper indentation
- No trailing whitespace
- RuboCop rules apply to embedded Ruby
- **Trailing commas required** in multiline hashes (`Style/TrailingCommaInHashLiteral`)

```erb
<%# CORRECT — trailing comma on last key-value pair %>
<%= pb_rails("title", props: {
  text: "Hello",
  size: 3,
}) %>

<%# WRONG — will fail RuboCop lint %>
<%= pb_rails("title", props: {
  text: "Hello",
  size: 3
}) %>
```

## Follow Component Patterns

Look at existing patterns in `components/` directory:
- `components/warranty/app/views/` - example view templates
- `components/sales/app/components/` - ViewComponent examples

## ViewComponent Integration

For complex components, use ViewComponent pattern:
```erb
<%# In view %>
<%= render MyComponent.new(title: "Hello") %>

<%# Component template (my_component.html.erb) %>
<%= pb_rails("card", props: { padding: "md" }) do %>
  <%= pb_rails("title", props: { text: @title, size: 4 }) %>
<% end %>
```

## Form Helpers

Use Rails form helpers with Playbook styling:
```erb
<%= form_with model: @user do |f| %>
  <%= pb_rails("text_input", props: {
    label: "Name",
    name: "user[name]",
    value: @user.name,
  }) %>
  <%= pb_rails("button", props: { text: "Save", type: "submit" }) %>
<% end %>
```

## Turbolinks Compatibility

Use `data-no-turbolink` for links to non-Turbolinks pages:
```erb
<div data-no-turbolink>
  <%= link_to "Old Page", old_path %>
</div>
```
